1
00:00:08,008 --> 00:00:09,908
Actually, it' a summer internship...

2
00:00:09,976 --> 00:00:13,241
but sky's the limit. That would be me,
you know? It's always....

3
00:00:13,313 --> 00:00:15,907
- What's going on?
- Come on. It's time.

4
00:00:15,982 --> 00:00:17,916
- Okay. Call me.
- I will.

5
00:00:18,485 --> 00:00:19,884
She's not gonna call me.

6
00:00:20,687 --> 00:00:22,416
Move. Watch it!

7
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:26,090
I didn't miss it, did I? Did I miss it?

8
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:29,152
No, you did not.

9
00:00:29,329 --> 00:00:31,422
- Where the hell is Blake?
- Late.

10
00:00:31,498 --> 00:00:34,865
- Why should tonight be different?
- Because it's our last night together.

11
00:00:34,934 --> 00:00:36,424
Hey, sorry I'm late.

12
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:38,527
- I ran into my ex.
Which one?

13
00:00:38,638 --> 00:00:41,505
To be honest,
I can't even tell them apart no more.

14
00:00:41,941 --> 00:00:43,499
All right, glasses up.

15
00:00:43,610 --> 00:00:47,410
Gentlemen, it took us four years.

16
00:00:47,514 --> 00:00:49,505
Excuse me, Ethan, five.

17
00:00:49,983 --> 00:00:52,975
But as of tonight, we are free men.

18
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:57,915
The scenery may change,
but our friendship won't.

19
00:00:59,025 --> 00:01:01,357
To the best night of our lives!

20
00:01:22,048 --> 00:01:23,640
Pretty out here.

21
00:01:24,217 --> 00:01:26,549
I should get outside more often.

22
00:01:27,220 --> 00:01:29,450
Harrison, I came here to talk.

23
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:32,585
Okay, someone dies, asks for help,
and you repeat a day.

24
00:01:32,659 --> 00:01:34,251
There, we talked.

25
00:01:34,327 --> 00:01:36,659
Not quite what I meant by talking.

26
00:01:37,230 --> 00:01:38,959
We all have our things:

27
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:41,865
Meredith has her drugs,
I have....

28
00:01:42,902 --> 00:01:44,733
I got everything else.

29
00:01:46,072 --> 00:01:47,630
And you got this:

30
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:51,642
your strange belief that you go back a day
and save innocent lives.

31
00:01:51,711 --> 00:01:53,804
I know where it comes from.

32
00:01:54,881 --> 00:01:57,475
No one expected you to save her, Tru.

33
00:01:57,951 --> 00:01:59,680
This is not about our mother.

34
00:01:59,752 --> 00:02:02,277
I took a semester of psych
back in high school.

35
00:02:02,355 --> 00:02:04,846
It's always about
someone's mother.

36
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:09,789
Maybe you should just try
and leave the past alone.

37
00:02:11,097 --> 00:02:12,462
I can't...

38
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,798
because it won't leave me alone.

39
00:02:34,087 --> 00:02:35,076
Help me.

40
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:04,646
Who would have thought of hiding
the spare under the doormat?

41
00:03:04,717 --> 00:03:08,153
You might consider a lighting fixture.
Both unique and efficient.

42
00:03:08,221 --> 00:03:10,155
Please tell me you brought coffee.

43
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:14,054
Blueberry Danish,
tuna, dry on whole- wheat...

44
00:03:14,127 --> 00:03:16,960
and a veggie burrito
from that place you like on Larkin.

45
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:20,466
With your bizarre hours, I couldn't decide
what meal you'd be on by now.

46
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,330
You are a good woman.

47
00:03:22,502 --> 00:03:24,231
So, how are you?

48
00:03:25,004 --> 00:03:28,337
- Pick a subject.
- I'll take"Boys" for $200.

49
00:03:29,309 --> 00:03:33,609
Okay, I know Evans didn't end well,
but you have to get back out there.

50
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:36,511
I just read
in a very legitimate publication...

51
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:39,177
that one out of every seven guys
is a keeper.

52
00:03:39,252 --> 00:03:41,447
More like one in a million.

53
00:03:42,989 --> 00:03:44,786
Look, I gotta shower.

54
00:03:45,358 --> 00:03:48,088
Is there anything you want to say to me?

55
00:03:48,661 --> 00:03:51,391
Yes. Thank you for my breakfast goodies.

56
00:03:51,764 --> 00:03:53,288
You're welcome.

57
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:56,360
That's what friends are for.

58
00:04:09,849 --> 00:04:11,009
Nasty.

59
00:04:11,718 --> 00:04:13,242
Tru.

60
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:28,665
Gardez?

61
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:36,064
Oh, my God!

62
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:42,277
Is everything all right here?

63
00:04:42,348 --> 00:04:44,782
Yeah, Gardez is an ass.
Everything's normal.

64
00:04:44,851 --> 00:04:47,911
- You should've seen the look on her face.
- Hysterical.

65
00:04:47,987 --> 00:04:49,978
Tru, come on. Lighten up.

66
00:04:51,658 --> 00:04:54,593
Looks like I got a pickup. A real one.

67
00:04:57,163 --> 00:05:00,064
- You okay?
- Yeah, whatever.

68
00:05:02,068 --> 00:05:03,558
Davis, do you think he's right?

69
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:06,138
Do you think
I take everything too seriously?

70
00:05:06,205 --> 00:05:08,173
Gardez sees dead bodies.

71
00:05:08,675 --> 00:05:12,577
You see the people they used to be.
He doesn't understand that.

72
00:05:13,112 --> 00:05:14,477
But you do?

73
00:05:14,947 --> 00:05:17,177
Just don't let him get to you.

74
00:05:30,863 --> 00:05:32,387
Hi, come on in.

75
00:05:32,899 --> 00:05:35,595
I know we're all working late
these days, Meredith...

76
00:05:35,702 --> 00:05:37,431
but the firm's board is insisting...

77
00:05:37,537 --> 00:05:40,631
that we implement a random
drug- testing program for our employees.

78
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:41,764
Now?

79
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:46,945
Unbelievable. Can I have my assistant
back when he's done?

80
00:05:47,413 --> 00:05:50,746
Actually, we're all being tested.
Liability issue.

81
00:05:54,153 --> 00:05:57,520
Just check in at the table
in front of the restrooms.

82
00:05:58,224 --> 00:05:59,589
Yeah, sure.

83
00:06:08,134 --> 00:06:09,158
Nice.

84
00:06:13,172 --> 00:06:15,140
Did I do that yesterday?

85
00:06:15,274 --> 00:06:16,400
Harrison.

86
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:19,639
It's a reasonable question,
for someone like you.

87
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:23,474
- You gotta admit, it's frigging weird.
- I told you, not every day repeats.

88
00:06:23,549 --> 00:06:26,518
In fact, most of them don't.
That's too bad.

89
00:06:26,586 --> 00:06:30,579
'Cause if your little fantasy was real,
today would be a hell of a day to do over.

90
00:06:30,656 --> 00:06:33,921
- What do you mean?
- You know, the whole Meredith thing.

91
00:06:34,794 --> 00:06:36,227
She didn't tell you?

92
00:06:36,295 --> 00:06:38,525
Drug test at her office today.

93
00:06:38,698 --> 00:06:40,757
She failed it and they fired her.

94
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:43,301
Oh, my God.
So you see my point?

95
00:06:43,436 --> 00:06:46,803
You could actually go back today,
bail Meredith out...

96
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:49,700
and we wouldn't be
having this conversation.

97
00:06:49,809 --> 00:06:52,073
Harrison, I can't control when it happens.

98
00:06:52,145 --> 00:06:54,443
So what do we do?
Nothing tonight.

99
00:06:54,514 --> 00:06:57,813
We'll check in with her tomorrow.
See how she's doing.

100
00:06:58,851 --> 00:07:02,309
What if tomorrow is just today
all over again?

101
00:07:02,722 --> 00:07:04,383
Bite me, Harrison.

102
00:07:06,025 --> 00:07:07,356
Can I ask you a question?

103
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:09,088
Sure, Davis, anything.

104
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:11,562
Does this lab coat make me look portly?

105
00:07:11,631 --> 00:07:13,690
No, you look fine.

106
00:07:13,766 --> 00:07:16,735
I just overheard you mention
that black was more....

107
00:07:16,803 --> 00:07:18,236
I think you called it"slimming."

108
00:07:18,304 --> 00:07:21,398
I was gonna see
if they came in a different color, maybe.

109
00:07:25,211 --> 00:07:27,805
Gardez must have been driving
all over the city.

110
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:30,405
Actually, they all came in
on the same pickup.

111
00:07:30,483 --> 00:07:33,452
It's five dead males, mid- to- late- 20s.

112
00:07:33,553 --> 00:07:36,852
Time of death is between 10:30 and 1 1:00.

113
00:07:37,890 --> 00:07:41,257
I lifted the personals,
if you want to start bagging.

114
00:07:41,694 --> 00:07:44,720
Any lDs?
Wallets were missing.

115
00:07:45,565 --> 00:07:49,831
The prelim tox report shows four of them
had pretty high levels of alcohol.

116
00:07:49,936 --> 00:07:52,632
Enough to kill them?
Probably not.

117
00:07:52,738 --> 00:07:55,229
But there is something strange
about this fifth guy.

118
00:07:55,341 --> 00:07:57,605
He had no alcohol in his system...

119
00:07:57,677 --> 00:08:00,874
but he did have a trace
of a chemical called Avlocardyl.

120
00:08:00,947 --> 00:08:02,608
One of them was married.

121
00:08:02,715 --> 00:08:05,513
That's a shame.
What else can you tell me?

122
00:08:12,091 --> 00:08:14,582
And one of them was making friends.

123
00:08:24,103 --> 00:08:26,469
Is there anything you want to say to me?

124
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:28,067
I suck.

125
00:08:32,411 --> 00:08:33,571
Hello.

126
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:38,011
- I'm looking for Gardez. Is he....
- Out on a pickup.

127
00:08:38,951 --> 00:08:41,385
Can I take a message?
Sure, yeah.

128
00:08:42,154 --> 00:08:45,453
I'm a friend of a friend.
He hooked me up with a job interview...

129
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,117
and in case I don't get the gig...

130
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:49,388
I thought I'd thank him
while I was still in town.

131
00:08:49,462 --> 00:08:52,829
Job interview. Those are always fun.
What was it for?

132
00:08:53,132 --> 00:08:55,362
Photographer.
Postmortem?

133
00:08:55,601 --> 00:08:58,331
Crime scene. Upstairs. Sheriff's office.

134
00:08:58,437 --> 00:09:01,099
Right, of course. How'd it go?

135
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:02,841
I don't know.

136
00:09:03,075 --> 00:09:05,441
I was meeting with the Sheriff
about half an hour.

137
00:09:05,511 --> 00:09:08,674
Then I walked out and realized
I had something stuck in my teeth.

138
00:09:08,748 --> 00:09:09,976
Sexy.

139
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:13,608
I'm not sure the Sheriff thought so.

140
00:09:14,954 --> 00:09:17,616
I should get your name for the message.

141
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:19,817
It's Luc, with a"C."

142
00:09:20,826 --> 00:09:22,589
Tru, with a"U."

143
00:09:22,662 --> 00:09:24,687
Is this man bothering you?

144
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:29,189
Yes, Davis. Please have him escorted
from the building.

145
00:09:29,635 --> 00:09:30,829
Really?
No.

146
00:09:30,937 --> 00:09:33,770
- Davis, this is Luc.
- Yeah, we met earlier.

147
00:09:33,873 --> 00:09:37,570
I got lost on my way to the interview.
Thanks for the directions.

148
00:09:37,677 --> 00:09:42,171
I'm sure Gardez will be back pretty soon,
if you just want to hang out till--

149
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,476
<i>HeIp me. </i>

150
00:09:46,953 --> 00:09:48,215
You okay?

151
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:52,949
Yeah, I'm fine. I just have to--
<i>HeIp me. </i>

152
00:10:01,067 --> 00:10:03,535
Would you mind waiting here
for one second?

153
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:06,097
I just need to....I'm sorry.

154
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:08,698
Excuse me, Davis.

155
00:10:10,810 --> 00:10:12,277
She does that a lot.

156
00:10:42,174 --> 00:10:44,301
- Help me.
- Save us.

157
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:45,909
- We need you.

158
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:47,673
- Please.

159
00:10:48,848 --> 00:10:50,076
- Help me.

160
00:11:01,627 --> 00:11:05,119
Who would have thought of putting
the spare key under the doormat?

161
00:11:05,197 --> 00:11:06,596
Very clever.

162
00:11:06,899 --> 00:11:09,561
Okay, so I brought you....

163
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:12,729
Blueberry Danish, tuna on whole- wheat,
and a veggie burrito?

164
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:17,002
- Okay, how'd you know that?
- The same way I know it's your birthday.

165
00:11:17,376 --> 00:11:19,503
My God, you remembered.

166
00:11:20,446 --> 00:11:22,573
<i>The sad thing is no one eIse did. </i>

167
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:26,678
- Thank you.
- Of course. How could I forget?

168
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:37,488
Harrison, I don't need you to believe me.
I just need your help.

169
00:11:37,563 --> 00:11:41,260
This is the first time it wasn't
just one body asking for help. It was five.

170
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:43,699
I didn't see their faces,
they came with no lDs...

171
00:11:43,803 --> 00:11:46,897
which means it's gonna be
five times harder for me to save them.

172
00:11:47,006 --> 00:11:48,166
I gotta be honest.

173
00:11:48,274 --> 00:11:50,435
It's early in the day
to have this conversation.

174
00:11:50,509 --> 00:11:54,309
I think one of them was poisoned, but
I've no idea what happened to the others.

175
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:57,975
- And you're telling me this because....
- Because I need info...

176
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:00,245
and you're more familiar with this world
than I am.

177
00:12:00,319 --> 00:12:03,413
Listen, Starsky,
if you're asking me to be your Hutch...

178
00:12:03,489 --> 00:12:06,424
I'm gonna have to say,
"Thanks, but no, thanks."

179
00:12:09,361 --> 00:12:10,953
Strippers, Harr?

180
00:12:12,098 --> 00:12:13,998
Okay. I'm in.

181
00:12:20,506 --> 00:12:25,034
I was wondering if you could tell me
where I could find a girl named Turquoise?

182
00:12:26,545 --> 00:12:28,479
We don't give that information
to customers.

183
00:12:28,547 --> 00:12:31,744
- I'm not really a customer.
- You here to audition?

184
00:12:31,851 --> 00:12:34,911
- Do I look like a stripper to you?
- A little bit.

185
00:12:42,194 --> 00:12:44,253
I thought you said
bartenders knew everything.

186
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:46,127
I got nowhere with that guy.

187
00:12:46,198 --> 00:12:49,599
- Did you work it?
- What do you mean"work it"?

188
00:12:50,136 --> 00:12:52,764
You gotta have an angle
to get information, Tru.

189
00:12:52,872 --> 00:12:55,500
By the way,
that Turquoise girl you're looking for?

190
00:12:55,608 --> 00:12:56,836
Her real name is Tara.

191
00:12:56,909 --> 00:12:59,901
She's got a day job doing telemarketing
in the Hancock Building.

192
00:12:59,979 --> 00:13:01,105
No way!

193
00:13:01,914 --> 00:13:05,475
Come on, Tru.
You know I got a way with the ladies.

194
00:13:06,352 --> 00:13:08,149
<i>My friend here toId me everything. </i>

195
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:11,417
Harrison, thank you. Seriously.
I'll call you later, okay?

196
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:14,857
Right, yeah. I'm right behind you.
I'm just gonna....

197
00:13:16,562 --> 00:13:20,396
I'm just gonna stay, and check it out here.
What's up?

198
00:13:21,934 --> 00:13:23,697
She's right over there.

199
00:13:24,937 --> 00:13:27,804
I just need to take down
your information.

200
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:32,443
- Tara?
- Yes.

201
00:13:33,512 --> 00:13:36,743
Hi, I'm putting together a little party...

202
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:39,842
and was wondering
if you were booked for the night?

203
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:43,252
- I'm sorry?
- Or are you working at the club?

204
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:50,693
Why are you coming in here
and asking me questions like that?

205
00:13:50,763 --> 00:13:52,060
I'm sorry, my bad.

206
00:13:52,131 --> 00:13:53,894
I didn't know how--
It's okay.

207
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:58,494
It's just that no one here
really knows what my other job is.

208
00:13:59,138 --> 00:14:00,230
I can relate.

209
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:02,967
But anyway, I am booked for the night.

210
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:07,244
Got an out- call gig.
Some bachelor party at the Pierpont.

211
00:14:07,313 --> 00:14:09,110
A bachelor party.

212
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:11,649
Would you happen to know
who hired you?

213
00:14:11,717 --> 00:14:14,379
Everything's handled by a booking service.

214
00:14:14,453 --> 00:14:17,479
- Right.
- Look, I gotta get back to work.

215
00:14:17,890 --> 00:14:20,882
Good luck with whatever it is
you're planning.

216
00:14:22,828 --> 00:14:26,025
Can I help you?
I'm here about the bachelor party.

217
00:14:26,098 --> 00:14:29,431
Right, Room 1712. It's called for 7:00...

218
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:33,301
but the entertainment
doesn't usually get here until after dark.

219
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:35,704
Why does everyone think
I look like a stripper?

220
00:14:35,774 --> 00:14:38,675
It's a bachelor party.
Who else would you be?

221
00:14:38,744 --> 00:14:40,405
Right, good point.

222
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:43,513
So help me out, you know,
to know what to expect.

223
00:14:43,582 --> 00:14:46,779
Is there anyone else working the party?
A waiter, bartender?

224
00:14:46,852 --> 00:14:49,150
They've declined those options.

225
00:14:49,355 --> 00:14:52,290
So no one but the guests
will be in the room tonight?

226
00:14:52,358 --> 00:14:54,826
- And you.
- And me.

227
00:14:55,294 --> 00:14:56,420
And one more thing.

228
00:14:56,495 --> 00:15:00,158
I had a question for the groom,
but I can't seem to find his number.

229
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:03,793
It's not our practice
to give out guests' personal information.

230
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:07,999
Too bad. He hadn't decided
whether he wants me naughty or nice.

231
00:15:12,378 --> 00:15:14,539
There's no way
I'll cancel my bachelor party.

232
00:15:14,613 --> 00:15:17,514
- It's my last night of freedom.
- No, you don't understand.

233
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:20,313
No, I think I do.
Robin sent you, didn't she?

234
00:15:20,386 --> 00:15:21,410
No, that's not--

235
00:15:21,487 --> 00:15:23,318
She hates it that I'm having this party...

236
00:15:23,389 --> 00:15:26,017
almost as much as she hates
the guys I invited.

237
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:27,820
Robin's not a fan of your friends?

238
00:15:27,893 --> 00:15:29,918
Okay, now this is starting to freak me out.

239
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:32,361
If Robin didn't send you,
then who the hell are you?

240
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:35,298
I'm with the hotel,
and there's a problem with your room, sir.

241
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:38,427
So they sent me personally
to explain the situation.

242
00:15:38,537 --> 00:15:41,028
- What's wrong with the room?
- We're overbooked.

243
00:15:41,140 --> 00:15:44,507
It has been way too long
since these guys have gotten together.

244
