00:32:10,495 --> 00:32:14,727
Obviously, something's up in your life.
I don't know if you're in trouble.

479
00:32:14,799 --> 00:32:19,293
I just hope that one day you'll realize
you can be honest with me.

480
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:06,277
- Maybe I didn't make myself clear.
- Maybe I wasn't listening.

481
00:33:06,351 --> 00:33:10,117
I know something happened in college
and what you're willing to do to cover up.

482
00:33:10,188 --> 00:33:13,316
No one knows anything
except the five guys in that room.

483
00:33:13,424 --> 00:33:16,052
What happened to the girl? Who was she?

484
00:33:16,127 --> 00:33:19,563
- You can't hide from the past.
- Don't you think I know that?

485
00:33:20,365 --> 00:33:22,890
Was it Ethan? What did he say?

486
00:33:22,967 --> 00:33:25,026
No, nothing. He just....

487
00:33:28,239 --> 00:33:29,263
lce.

488
00:33:31,776 --> 00:33:35,007
I thought it was you,
but you didn't plan tonight, did you?

489
00:33:35,079 --> 00:33:37,240
No. What does that have to do
with anything?

490
00:33:38,916 --> 00:33:40,508
<i>Don't know</i>
<i>what you're up to...</i>

491
00:33:40,585 --> 00:33:44,021
but I finally found Robin Wilson.
Only she isn't any bride.

492
00:33:44,088 --> 00:33:45,282
- Who's that?
- What?

493
00:33:45,356 --> 00:33:47,119
Get off the phone. Now.

494
00:33:47,191 --> 00:33:50,160
She caught the guy cheating on her,
called the wedding off.

495
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:52,526
- That was three months ago.
- Right.

496
00:33:53,898 --> 00:33:56,423
You've got 10 seconds to explain yourself.

497
00:33:56,501 --> 00:33:58,526
This isn't a bachelor party, Blake.

498
00:33:58,603 --> 00:34:00,764
The wedding was called off months ago.

499
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:03,238
That's crazy.
Why else would John want us all here?

500
00:34:03,307 --> 00:34:06,208
Because you share a secret
he doesn't want you to tell.

501
00:34:06,277 --> 00:34:10,737
Whatever happened in college, whatever
happened to that girl, it was John.

502
00:34:11,849 --> 00:34:13,248
John did it.

503
00:34:16,754 --> 00:34:18,346
Let me help you.

504
00:34:28,699 --> 00:34:32,328
What's she still doing here?
I thought I told you to get rid of her.

505
00:34:32,403 --> 00:34:35,099
She's got an interesting story
you all might want to hear.

506
00:34:35,206 --> 00:34:38,607
Not to be a pain in the ass,
but we had her thrown out.

507
00:34:39,110 --> 00:34:43,547
- Now you want us to listen to her?
- I think we've all been silent long enough.

508
00:34:45,450 --> 00:34:47,577
This isn't a bachelor party.

509
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:50,987
Not anymore.

510
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:55,856
You scared off the stripper,
we're running out of booze--

511
00:34:56,060 --> 00:34:59,461
John and his fiancée broke up months ago.

512
00:34:59,897 --> 00:35:01,865
Any of you guys know that?

513
00:35:04,802 --> 00:35:06,531
Is that true, John?

514
00:35:07,872 --> 00:35:10,500
Look, I can explain everything.

515
00:35:15,513 --> 00:35:16,980
Come on, guys.

516
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:21,745
The best night of our lives, remember?

517
00:35:28,526 --> 00:35:29,993
Thanks, guys.

518
00:35:32,363 --> 00:35:34,957
- No, don't.
- Just give me a minute.

519
00:35:40,037 --> 00:35:41,629
Going somewhere?

520
00:35:42,907 --> 00:35:44,966
What's the point in hanging around?

521
00:35:45,076 --> 00:35:47,601
You embarrassed me
in front of my friends.

522
00:35:47,712 --> 00:35:49,771
They can't be that good friends, John.

523
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:52,782
They still thought
you were getting married.

524
00:35:55,253 --> 00:35:57,585
It's not exactly an easy thing...

525
00:35:57,788 --> 00:36:00,882
to admit that your relationship failed,
you know?

526
00:36:01,526 --> 00:36:03,960
I was gonna tell them all tonight.

527
00:36:07,465 --> 00:36:09,490
I thought everybody
could use a good party.

528
00:36:09,567 --> 00:36:11,432
With plenty of drinks.

529
00:36:12,103 --> 00:36:13,866
On the rocks, right?

530
00:36:14,138 --> 00:36:17,005
God, that's a long way to go
to cover up a murder.

531
00:36:17,108 --> 00:36:21,374
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Let me fill you in on a few things.

532
00:36:21,445 --> 00:36:25,176
The first is one of your friends
wasn't drinking alcohol tonight.

533
00:36:25,316 --> 00:36:28,513
So, sure,
he's got the Avlocardyl in his system...

534
00:36:28,586 --> 00:36:30,850
but without the alcohol to hide it...

535
00:36:30,922 --> 00:36:34,358
at some point,
someone's gonna figure out what you did.

536
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:38,757
And second,
it's a little bartending trick I picked up.

537
00:36:39,397 --> 00:36:41,957
Even if you're drinking it straight,
like you...

538
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:43,796
if you want to keep the drink cool...

539
00:36:43,868 --> 00:36:47,065
you shake a little crushed ice
in the bottom of the glass.

540
00:36:47,338 --> 00:36:49,829
<i>Yes, every gIass, John. </i>

541
00:36:50,308 --> 00:36:52,572
Of course, if you didn't mess with the ice...

542
00:36:52,677 --> 00:36:56,841
then you won't need the antidote
your best man has in the next room.

543
00:37:31,082 --> 00:37:33,915
- Five years late.
That's what I don't get.

544
00:37:34,218 --> 00:37:36,413
Why now, after all this time?

545
00:37:36,554 --> 00:37:39,853
Three weeks ago, I sent him a letter
saying I was going to the police.

546
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:40,982
You?

547
00:37:41,892 --> 00:37:44,019
I couldn't take it anymore...

548
00:37:44,695 --> 00:37:48,256
and I tried to make it right.
lnstead, I almost got us all killed.

549
00:37:48,332 --> 00:37:49,822
What happened?

550
00:37:51,269 --> 00:37:52,793
Catherine Hill.

551
00:37:55,873 --> 00:37:59,468
We didn't even know her name
until we read it in the papers.

552
00:37:59,577 --> 00:38:03,741
She was a freshman, made the mistake
of coming to a graduation party.

553
00:38:04,949 --> 00:38:06,382
<i>John got her aIone in a room. </i>

554
00:38:06,450 --> 00:38:08,680
It's a little close, isn't it?

555
00:38:09,153 --> 00:38:12,714
That hurts. Stop it. I told you, no!

556
00:38:13,991 --> 00:38:16,789
- Who said it was up to you?
- Let go of me.

557
00:38:23,601 --> 00:38:26,229
A girlfriend once said he slapped her.

558
00:38:26,404 --> 00:38:28,838
He denied it and we believed him.

559
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:33,700
When he told us what happened that night
was an accident, we didn't believe him.

560
00:38:33,811 --> 00:38:35,711
<i>We didn't say anything. </i>

561
00:38:37,348 --> 00:38:38,713
<i>To anybody. </i>

562
00:38:39,383 --> 00:38:41,977
And you sent a letter? That's something.

563
00:38:42,053 --> 00:38:44,146
I didn't have the guts to sign it.

564
00:38:44,221 --> 00:38:46,655
He didn't know which one of us
was turning him in.

565
00:38:46,724 --> 00:38:48,919
So he had to kill all of you.

566
00:38:50,394 --> 00:38:53,830
I'm sorry for not trusting you.
But with everything...

567
00:38:54,565 --> 00:38:56,430
I barely trust myself.

568
00:38:57,768 --> 00:38:59,736
You did the right thing.

569
00:39:00,338 --> 00:39:02,101
Five years too late.

570
00:39:25,763 --> 00:39:27,526
Surprise!

571
00:39:31,869 --> 00:39:33,166
Surprise!

572
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:51,344
Tru.

573
00:40:10,674 --> 00:40:13,165
- You need something?
- How'd you know?

574
00:40:16,347 --> 00:40:18,611
You take the fun out of everything.

575
00:40:18,682 --> 00:40:20,343
It was fun for me.

576
00:40:24,021 --> 00:40:25,045
Hello?

577
00:40:25,122 --> 00:40:29,183
I'm sure you won't be surprised to hear
there was a drug test at my office.

578
00:40:30,995 --> 00:40:33,725
Obviously, you knew something
and opted not to tell me...

579
00:40:33,798 --> 00:40:37,063
so I just called specifically
to not say"thank you."

580
00:40:38,269 --> 00:40:40,760
<i>But in case you're curious, </i>
<i>I passed the test. </i>

581
00:40:40,838 --> 00:40:44,934
Maybe now you'll get off my back
and let my past stay in the past.

582
00:40:45,142 --> 00:40:48,976
Meredith, I wasn't trying to prove a point.
I was just trying to help.

583
00:40:49,046 --> 00:40:51,640
- And I did, didn't I?
- Good night, Tru.

584
00:40:57,655 --> 00:41:00,215
- You wanted to see me?
- Close the door.

585
00:41:04,562 --> 00:41:06,894
Thanks for covering that
for me.

586
00:41:07,832 --> 00:41:09,197
No problem.

587
00:41:09,533 --> 00:41:12,627
I've never been paid
to provide a sample before.

588
00:41:13,838 --> 00:41:18,172
But I gotta ask, how did you know
there was gonna be a drug test today?

589
00:41:19,310 --> 00:41:21,107
I just had a feeling.

590
00:41:28,686 --> 00:41:30,244
I just don't get it.

591
00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:33,051
I went through all this
to save these five guys...

592
00:41:33,123 --> 00:41:36,957
and now there's a chance they'll go to jail.
What's the point?

593
00:41:37,828 --> 00:41:40,626
Look, Tru, this thing you're dealing with....

594
00:41:41,632 --> 00:41:45,068
Maybe for you,
it's about more than just saving people.

595
00:41:45,569 --> 00:41:49,027
See, these guys had a secret,
and they put it to rest.

596
00:41:49,106 --> 00:41:51,040
Maybe, I don't know....

597
00:41:51,542 --> 00:41:53,976
Maybe you can try and do the same.

598
00:41:56,247 --> 00:41:58,374
So Lindsay has this theory.

599
00:41:58,916 --> 00:42:01,680
One out of every seven guys is a good one.

600
00:42:02,253 --> 00:42:05,313
I've spent an entire evening
with six guys that were bad.

601
00:42:05,389 --> 00:42:07,619
So does that make you Number Seven?

602
00:42:09,226 --> 00:42:10,955
I wouldn't bet on it.

603
00:42:11,829 --> 00:42:13,456
Don't worry, Tru.

604
00:42:14,298 --> 00:42:15,822
He's out there.

605
00:42:32,082 --> 00:42:33,549
You know him?

606
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:35,116
No, not yet.